#Text=Well that might have happened in West Virginia , where there was more voters that participated in the Democratic primary than the Republican primary .
#Text=So what is your reaction to the showing of prison inmate Keith Russell Judd in that primary ?
#Text=[ The American people ] may not be able to articulate it the way I just did but they know in their heart what 's true and what is n't .
#Text=And they know for sure that [ President Obama 's ] not on their side .
#Text=And they 're right .
#Text=Well it shows that Obama 's left a void .
#Text=His lack of leadership has left a void and people are upset .
#Text=He should be out there with the people .
#Text=He should be in those coal mines .
#Text=He should be in those towns , where those factories have left , and he ought to be out there with the homeowners who 've been foreclosed on by his campaign contributors .
#Text=People know this man is nothing but a Wall Street creature .

#Text=They know that his advisers in the White House are all failed executives of failed banks that have been bailed out : people like Emil [ Michael ] , people like [ Jacob ] Lew , [ William ] Daley , they 're all from the big six : the big corporations we had to bail out .
#Text=Yes .
#Text=What did they get for their failures ?
#Text=Promoted to the White House .
#Text=People know that .
#Text=Most of the guys who are raising his campaign money .
#Text=They 're sick of it .
#Text=And that 's why people in West Virginia , and lot of the blue collar people do n't like Obama .
#Text=It 's his own fault because he is not of the people .
#Text=He is of Wall Street .
#Text=People are finally starting to see that .
#Text=John Wolfe is n't [ of Wall Street ] .
#Text=John Wolfe worked his way up through .
#Text=I 've worked in factories .
#Text=I 've worked in grocery stores .
#Text=I almost cut my thumb off doing agricultural work .
#Text=When I went to college , I did n't have any transportation .
#Text=I had to hitchhike up and down I75 to get an education .
#Text=So I know what it 's like to work in the real world .
#Text=I know what it 's like to have to strive hard to get ahead .
#Text=But Obama does n't relate to those people .
#Text=He 's too professorial .
#Text=He 's too detached .
#Text=He is of Wall Street .
#Text=Those are the people he pals around with : Bob Wolf
#Text=that Swiss banker is his favorite guy .
#Text=The guy that loves speculation on Wall Street .
#Text=He gets paid billions and billions of dollars for failed banks to get back up .
#Text=Him and Obama are like twins .
#Text=I mean you see Bob Wolf , you see Obama .
#Text=I mean , this is the sort of thing people sense .
#Text=They may not be able to articulate it the way I just did but they know in their heart what 's true and what is n't .
#Text=And they know for sure that he 's not on their side .
#Text=And they 're right .
